Aspects of globalization, sustainability, technological material and system advances and modes of interdisciplinarity are driving forces for the development of the proposed High-Rise Traffic-Port systems prototype that uses fewer resources and adapts efficiently to differing urban sites and programmatic requirements. The design results from the integrative development of its influential components: the environmentally friendly air-transfer network that enables an experiential bridging of urban sites while preserving visual, spatial and time perceptions in human scale; the adaptable high-rise structures that serve as vertical airport elements with inherent geometrical and mechanical features of deploy-ability, vertical expansion, modular assembly, reliability under differing heights and environmental conditions, re-usability of the lightweight components
